In Kali, open a terminal window and run the following commands:

    adduser tdh Add a user for remote login. Set a password and other info.
    usermod -aG sudo tdh Get an updated list of installable packages
    systemctl start ssh Start the base ssh server

You can use putty on windows to connect to kali over ssh

You can auto start with the command

systemctl enable ssh

And this conclude the guide Enabling Remote Desktop and SSH access to Kali. Do not forget to reboot and to upgrade your machine.
